]][[!template id=landing_page_section_slides_item_cuartos.tmpl 
  
  cid=1
  class="slide-red"
  content="""
### We develop digitization devices

We engineer and manufacture ([open-hardware](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_hardware)) digitization systems designed 
to scan documents that, due to their format, dimensions, or fragility, are unsuitable for conventional scanning equipment. 
Our digitization rigs are designed for local fabrication using accessible tools and materials, following [appropriate technology](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appropriate_technology) 
principles. We also develop and customize [open-source software](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software) solutions for image acquisition and post-processing workflows.
"""
  item1_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/v-coop_550.jpg"
  item1_txt="<span>V-shaped cradle device for bound material installed in IdelCoop's digitization laboratory (2022)</span>"
  item2_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/memoria.jpg"
  item2_txt="<span>Copy stand for large-format documents installed at the Ex-ESMA (Memoria Abierta, 2021)</span>"
  item3_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/cenital-moderno_550.jpg"
  item3_txt="<span>Laser-cut copy stand for loose documents (Museo de Arte Moderno de Buenos Aires, 2017)</span>"
  item4_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/cnba_500.jpg"
  item4_txt="<span>V-shaped cradle stand made with 'pine-clear' wood slats (Colegio Nacional Buenos Aires, 2014)</span>"
  
]][[!template id=landing_page_section_slides_item_cuartos.tmpl 
  
  cid=2
  class="slide-red"
  margin_left=1
  content="""
### We implement digital collection management systems.

Using platforms specifically designed for this purpose —such as [Collective Access](https://collectiveacces.bibliohack.org/)— we enable flexible structuring of information while complying with established archival and documentation standards.
These tools facilitate essential tasks such as acquisitions, removals, and location tracking. 
Our services include system deployment, data migration from diverse formats and scales, and the development of customized frontend interfaces tailored to current usability and design standards.
"""
  item1_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/collective.jpg"
  item1_txt="<span>Cover of the digital catalog of the Museo de Arte Moderno de Buenos Aires</span>"
  item2_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/chambi-detail_550.jpg"
  item2_txt="<span>Browse view of the collection of photographer Martín Chambi (Peru)</span>"
  item3_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/archivociudad_visor_550.jpg"
  item3_txt="<span>Website of Archivo Historico de la Ciudad de Buenos Aires collection (Multimedia browser view)</span>"
  item4_img="/uploads/landing_page/tecnologia_abierta/inm-detalle_550.jpg"
  item4_txt="<span>Detail of the sound recording from the digital catalogue of Instituto Nacional de la Música</span>"


]][[!template  id=landing_page_section_slides_item_single.tmpl 

  cid=3
  class="slide-gray"
  content="""
### Training and Consulting

We provide specialized training for personnel involved in digitization workflows, including the operation of scanning rigs, cameras, lighting setups, and image capture software. 
Our training extends to the development of digitization protocols aligned with best practices, as well as the administration of digital collection management systems. 
We also offer consulting for the formulation of grant proposals, strategic planning of digitization initiatives, and advanced archival tasks such as metadata schema design and data modeling.

""" 
  img="/uploads/landing_page/capacitacion/capac_filo.jpg"
  caption_txt="Training for the Research Institutes of the Faculty of Philosophy and Letters of the UBA (2018)"

]][[!template  id=landing_page_section_slides_item_cuartos.tmpl 

  cid=4
  class="slide-gray"
  margin_left=1
  content="""
### Presentations and Events

We participate in and collaborate on organizing events open to information professionals, researchers, public officials, and activists to reflect on topics that concern and interest us: 
digital transformation in cultural institutions; 
digital heritage management policies in both the public and private sectors; 
the tensions between access and intellectual property; and the use of data in today's challenging technological landscape shaped by LLMs.
"""
  item1_img="/uploads/landing_page/politicas/matias-neuquen.jpg"
  item1_txt="'How to Build Digital Collections in Libraries and Archives', organized by the Neuquen Legislature (Neuquen, 2020)"
